<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Value handle that asserts if the Value is deleted.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is a Value Handle that points to a value and asserts out if the value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is destroyed while the handle is still live.  This is very useful for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><Highlight kind="comment">/// catching dangling pointer bugs and other things which can be non-obvious.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><Highlight kind="comment">/// One particularly useful place to use this is as the Key of a map.  Dangling</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pointer bugs often lead to really subtle bugs that only occur if another</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><Highlight kind="comment">/// object happens to get allocated to the same address as the old one.  Using</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><Highlight kind="comment">/// an AssertingVH ensures that an assert is triggered as soon as the bad</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><Highlight kind="comment">/// delete occurs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that an AssertingVH handle does &#42;not&#42; follow values across RAUW</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="256"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operations.  This means that RAUW&#39;s need to explicitly update the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="257"><Highlight kind="comment">/// AssertingVH&#39;s as it moves.  This is required because in non-assert mode this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="258"><Highlight kind="comment">/// class turns into a trivial wrapper around a pointer.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ValueTy&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/assertingvh"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/assertingvh/#a3bd43ce6246df58d73ff9f0fa3a025b2">AssertingVH</a></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Value handle that tracks a Value across RAUW.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="comment">/// TrackingVH is designed for situations where a client needs to hold a handle</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to a Value (or subclass) across some operations which may move that value,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="comment">/// but should never destroy it or replace it with some unacceptable type.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It is an error to attempt to replace a value with one of a type which is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">/// incompatible with any of its outstanding TrackingVHs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It is an error to read from a TrackingVH that does not point to a valid</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="comment">/// value.  A TrackingVH is said to not point to a valid value if either it</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><Highlight kind="comment">/// hasn&#39;t yet been assigned a value yet or because the value it was tracking</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// may call any non-virtual Value method on getValPtr(), but no subclass</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// methods.  If WeakTrackingVH were implemented as a CallbackVH, it would use</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// this</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Called when this-&gt;getValPtr()-&gt;replaceAllUsesWith(new&#95;value) is called,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#95;before&#95; any of the uses have actually been replaced.  If WeakTrackingVH</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// were</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// implemented as a CallbackVH, it would use this method to call</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// setValPtr(new&#95;value).  AssertingVH would do nothing in this method.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callbackvh/#a1f633ad5396b6726039d26f5bbac940d"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">virtual</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callbackvh/#a1f633ad5396b6726039d26f5bbac940d">allUsesReplacedWith</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/valuehandlebase/#aeceedf6e1a7d48a588516ce2b1983d6f">Value</a> &#42;) &#123;&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Value handle that poisons itself if the Value is deleted.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is a Value Handle that points to a value and poisons itself if the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"><Highlight kind="comment">/// value is destroyed while the handle is still live.  This is very useful for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><Highlight kind="comment">/// catching dangling pointer bugs where an \\c AssertingVH cannot be used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><Highlight kind="comment">/// because the dangling handle needs to outlive the value without ever being</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><Highlight kind="comment">/// used.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434"><Highlight kind="comment">/// One particularly useful place to use this is as the Key of a map. Dangling</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pointer bugs often lead to really subtle bugs that only occur if another</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><Highlight kind="comment">/// object happens to get allocated to the same address as the old one. Using</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><Highlight kind="comment">/// a PoisoningVH ensures that an assert is triggered if looking up a new value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><Highlight kind="comment">/// in the map finds a handle from the old value.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="439"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="440"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that a PoisoningVH handle does &#42;not&#42; follow values across RAUW</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operations. This means that RAUW&#39;s need to explicitly update the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">/// PoisoningVH&#39;s as it moves. This is required because in non-assert mode this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">/// class turns into a trivial wrapper around a pointer.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ValueTy&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/poisoningvh"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/poisoningvh/#a32ad059aca7204b24d7077172709e537">PoisoningVH</a> final</Highlight></CodeLine>
